{
  "texts": [
    "Metrics for Evaluating Digital Twin GenerationEvaluating the performance of LLMs is non-trivial, particularly in conjunction with code generation tasks [99,100].",
    "The evaluation metrics used to assess the quality of an LLM can be categorized into three main types: similarity-based methods, execution-based methods, and LLM-as-judge approaches.Similarity-Based Methods.",
    "These metrics assess the generated output, produced by the LLM in response to a user's prompt, by comparing it to reference code.",
    "A commonly used metric is BLEU (Bilingual Evaluation Understudy) [101,102], which measures the n-gram overlap between the generated and reference texts.",
    "CodeBLEU extends BLEU by incorporating syntactic and semantic features specific to source code, thereby providing a more nuanced evaluation of programming tasks."
  ]
}